Since the radii of the small circles are all 3 units, the distance from $O$ to $T$ is $3+3=6$ units. Since $T$ is the midpoint of the line segment connecting the centers of the small circles, the distance from $O$ to the center of any small circle is 6 units. Therefore, the radius of the larger circle is $6+3=9$ units, and the diameter is $2(9)=\boxed{18}$ units.The answer is: 18

