label("$\theta$", A + (0.7,0.5));
label("$M$", M, E);
label("$O$", O, N);
label("$P$", P, S);
[/asy]

Let $M$ be the midpoint of $BC,$ let $O$ be the foot of the altitude from $A$ to $BC,$ and let $P$ be the foot of the altitude from $A$ to $MO.$  Since $MO$ is a median of triangle $ABC,$ $AP$ is an angle bisector of triangle $ABC.$

Let $OM = x.$  Then $AP = \frac{BC}{2} = 2x,$ so
\[\tan \theta = \frac{OM}{AP} = \frac{x}{2x} = \boxed{\frac{1}{2}}.\]The answer is: \frac{1}{2}

