Similarly, $G_B$ divides $MN$ in the ratio $2:1,$ $G_C$ divides $MN$ in the ratio $2:1,$ and $G_D$ divides $MN$ in the ratio $2:1.$  Hence, $G_A G_B G_C G_D$ is similar to $MNCD.$

The ratio of the area of $G_A G_B G_C G_D$ to the area of $MNCD$ is therefore $\left( \frac{2}{3} \right)^2 = \frac{4}{9}.$

Since $MNCD$ is similar to $ABCD,$ the ratio of the area of $MNCD$ to the area of $ABCD$ is $\left( \frac{1}{2} \right)^2 = \frac{1}{4}.$

Therefore, the ratio of the area of $G_A G_B G_C G_D$ to the area of $ABCD$ is
