[/asy]

Since the vertex angle of the cross-section triangle is 60 degrees, each base angle of the triangle is 30 degrees.
This means that the height of the triangle is half the length of the base, or $\frac{12\sqrt{3}}{2} = 6\sqrt{3}$ inches.

The radius of the sphere is the height of the triangle, or $6\sqrt{3}$ inches.

The volume of a sphere is given by $\frac{4}{3}\pi r^3$, so the volume of this sphere is $\frac{4}{3}\pi (6\sqrt{3})^3 = \frac{4}{3}\pi (216) = \boxed{288\pi}$ cubic inches.

The answer is: 288\pi

