content.solution_latex:
Since $AB$ and $CD$ are chords that meet at $P,$ $AP \cdot BP = CP \cdot DP.$
Then $3 \cdot BP = 8 \cdot DP,$ so $\frac{BP}{DP} = \boxed{\frac{8}{3}}.$
The answer is: \frac{8}{3}

