content.solution_latex:
Let $z = x + yi,$ where $x$ and $y$ are real numbers.  Then
\[|x + yi - 5 - i| = |(x - 5) + (y - 1)i| = \sqrt{(x - 5)^2 + (y - 1)^2} = 5.\]This is the equation of a circle centered at $(5,1)$ and with radius 5.  Note that the points $1 - 2i$ and $9 + 4i$ lie on this circle.

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

pair A, B, O, P, Q;

A = (1,-2);
B = (9,4);
O = (5,1);
P = (A + O)/2;
Q = (B + O)/2;

draw(Circle(O,5));
draw((0,0)--A--B--cycle);
draw(O--P);
draw(O--Q);

dot("$1 - 2i$", A, SW);
dot("$9 + 4i$", B, NE);
dot("$5 + i$", O, NE);
[/asy]

Let $P$ and $Q$ be the midpoints of the segments connecting $z$ to $1 - 2i$ and $9 + 4i,$ respectively.  Then
\begin{align*}
|z - 1 + 2i|^2 + |z - 9 - 4i|^2 &= |2z - (1 - 2i) - (9 + 4i)|^2 + |2z - (1 - 2i) - (9 + 4i)|^2 \\
&= 4 |z - 5 - i|^2 \\
&= 4 \cdot 5^2 \\
&= \boxed{100}.
\end{align*}The answer is: 100

